briefdescription.para: Macro used prior to declaring functions in the D-Bus header files.

detaileddescription.para: Expands to "extern "C"" when using a C++ compiler, and expands to nothing when using a C compiler.
Please don't use this in your own code, consider it D-Bus internal.

briefdescription.para: Macro used after declaring functions in the D-Bus header files.

detaileddescription.para: Expands to "}" when using a C++ compiler, and expands to nothing when using a C compiler.
Please don't use this in your own code, consider it D-Bus internal.

briefdescription.para: A null pointer, defined appropriately for C or C++.
Tells the compiler to warn about a function or type if it's used.

detaileddescription.para: Code marked in this way should also be enclosed in #ifndefDBUS_DISABLE_DEPRECATED deprecatedstuffhere #endif
Please don't use this in your own code, consider it D-Bus internal.

briefdescription.para: Tells gcc not to warn about extensions to the C standard in the following expression, even if compiling with -pedantic.

detaileddescription.para: Do not use this macro in your own code; please consider it to be internal to libdbus.

briefdescription.para: TRUE, FALSE, NULL, and so on
